subSubSection.paragraph:
Skeleton
.

An ectosomal skeleton of closely packed discotriaenes (
Fig. 10c
) with margins of neighbouring spicules overlapping. Desma skeleton strongly zygosed (
Fig. 11e
) with thick, strong tubercles. Smaller discotriaenes and subdermal desmas show occasional zygosis (
Fig. 11a
1
). Auxiliary spicules long thin oxeas (
Fig. 11c, 11c
1
), not prominent.
